00:30:19,778 --> 00:30:21,899
it doesn't give the publisher the right straight away

526
00:30:22,100 --> 00:30:23,300
to develop these future games,

527
00:30:23,781 --> 00:30:25,682
but it does give them the first in line

528
00:30:26,223 --> 00:30:27,844
or first opportunity to fund them

529
00:30:28,304 --> 00:30:29,985
and publish them if they want at a later date.

530
00:30:32,387 --> 00:30:35,110
They might also, especially for some larger publishers,

531
00:30:35,150 --> 00:30:37,273
they might want an option to acquire the game IP.

532
00:30:37,473 --> 00:30:39,375
So scrapping the exclusive license

533
00:30:39,455 --> 00:30:41,177
and going to the assignment we talked about earlier.

534
00:30:44,081 --> 00:30:44,822
They might want to do that

535
00:30:44,882 --> 00:30:46,524
so that they can control the franchise

536
00:30:46,584 --> 00:30:48,246
and create future games.

537
00:30:48,827 --> 00:30:50,669
You know, and they might see a real value in doing that.

538
00:30:51,833 --> 00:30:53,555
So similarly to the right of first refusal,

539
00:30:54,235 --> 00:30:56,297
the option is likely to be framed as a way

540
00:30:56,537 --> 00:30:58,439
of ensuring that the publisher is first in line

541
00:30:58,459 --> 00:30:59,941
should you decide to sell the IP

542
00:31:00,361 --> 00:31:02,483
or work with someone else to do something with it.

543
00:31:04,405 --> 00:31:06,807
Alternatively, it might just be a way

544
00:31:06,867 --> 00:31:08,709
that the developer has a right to negotiate you,

545
00:31:09,110 --> 00:31:11,132
negotiate with you about buying the IP

546
00:31:11,852 --> 00:31:13,073
during the term of the contract.

547
00:31:15,083 --> 00:31:23,549
And neither that right of first refusal or the option to buy your IP should continue or last beyond the term of the publishing agreement.

548
00:31:24,830 --> 00:31:31,475
So include and also include a time limit on the period of negotiations in respect of the right of first refusal and the option as well.

549
00:31:31,975 --> 00:31:40,361
That's going to keep both sides honest, and it prevents negotiations dragging on indefinitely that are another way of locking your rights and preventing you actually doing what you want to do.

550
00:31:44,072 --> 00:31:52,355
You should also check if the contract includes other restrictions that might prevent you from developing or releasing future projects, either indefinitely or for a limited time.

551
00:31:54,035 --> 00:32:02,518
Anything that stops you from doing something on an ongoing basis should be reduced or cut down to a defined period, so you know those restrictions are going to end at some point.

552
00:32:04,199 --> 00:32:11,202
The restriction shown here is aimed at protecting the publisher's investment in you and is to prevent you from leasing a similar game.

